        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 21 at 6:15PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 615 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Union, or 10 miles north of Eutaw, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Snoddy, Ralph, West Greene, Union, Fosters Boat Landing, McFarland
Mall, Kirk, Pleasant Ridge, Lewiston, Benevola, Johnston Lake, Eutaw,
Shelton State Community College, Elrod, New West Greene, Buhl, Gordo,
Mantua, Clinton, and Jena.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
